==English==
===Verb Phrase===
'''to see a man''' 
===Alternative Forms===
*'''to see a man about a dog'''
*'''to see a man about a horse'''

# to go have a drink or to meet one's bootlegger.
# to take one's leave for some urgent purpose, especially to go to the bathroom.
#a bland euphemism to conceal one's true purpose.

'''Quotations'''

*'''1867''' Although they were all out, at the bases, and the rest of our nine having gone to see a man there was nobody to take the bat. ''Ball Players' Chronicle 12 Sep. 3/I.''
*'''1948''' I'm in a rush--gotta see a dog about a man! ''Chigago Tribune 21 March (Comics) 15."

